<div class="comment" id="comment-47757617">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/bsimpson">bsimpson</a> 1 day ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">Finally!<p>I never understood the PR=branch model GitHub defaulted to.  Stacked commits (ala Phabricator&#x2F;Gerrit) always jived more with how my brain reasons about changes.<p>Glad to see this option.  I guess I&#x27;ll have to install their CLI thing now.</div>
